    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''After Sanctions, Doctors Get Drug Company Pay'' (front page, June 3):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''After Sanctions, Doctors Get Drug Company Pay'' (front page, June 3):</p>
        <p>People who participate as human subjects in medical research in treating mental illnesses are heroes who often make personal sacrifices for a greater good. They deserve the highest levels of clinical care and protection from potential harm.</p>
        <p>Physicians who have been convicted of criminal wrongdoing or otherwise sanctioned for unethical practices while engaged in research should not be permitted to conduct further research using human subjects.</p>
        <p>We all hope for better, safe and effective treatment options -- even a cure for mental illness -- but only if the clinical research rigorously reflects the highest ethical standards.</p>
        <p>Michael J. Fitzpatrick  Executive Director  National Alliance on Mental Illness  Arlington, Va., June 3, 2007</p>
      </block>
